---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Seats" description="Contest pages planned for candidates, results, boundaries, and local election signals.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Seats</p>
    <h1>Every contest needs the right geography.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The first data phase creates stable contest pages for constituencies, wards, divisions,
      lists, and authority-wide races before any live forecast is published.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="workflow">
      <article>
        <span>1</span>
        <h2>Identity</h2>
        <p>Official code, name, nation, authority, boundary generation, predecessor areas, and election cycle.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>2</span>
        <h2>Candidates</h2>
        <p>Candidate name, party, incumbency, source URL, publication timestamp, and withdrawal or replacement status.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>3</span>
        <h2>History</h2>
        <p>Borough, county, unitary, Westminster, Senedd, Scottish, mayoral, and by-election result links where they explain the contest.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>4</span>
        <h2>Signals</h2>
        <p>Polling, demographics, incumbency, candidate strength, local context, and model inputs with provenance and freshness labels.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
